nodes.description: The obsessive-compulsive chef with a love for cleaning almost as strong as her competitiveness.
King of sarcasm, notorious for his inability to cry and his mysteriously vague job in 'data reconfiguration and statistical factoring'.
Aspiring actor, food enthusiast, and charmer of women. Can be counted on to say 'How you doin'?' at least once per episode.
The dinosaur-loving, three-times divorced palaeontologist with an unyielding love for Rachel.
From spoiled daddy's girl to independent fashionista, she's the one Ross has been in love with since ninth grade.
The quirky masseuse/musician who can serenade you with a song about smelly cats or regale you with tales of her bizarre past.
Piano-playing divorcee who stole Phoebe's heart and had the courage to name a dog 'Clunkers'.
Central Perk’s barista sporting peroxide-blonde hair, pining away for Rachel behind the espresso machine.
Monica and Ross's mother, with a knack for backhanded compliments mostly aimed at Monica.
Ross's first ex-wife, who came out as a lesbian and made Ross a single dad.
Monica's older, mustachioed ex-boyfriend who makes Chandler incredibly insecure.
Chandler's loud and obnoxious on-again, off-again girlfriend. Known for her nasal laugh and the catchphrase, 'OH. MY. GOD.'
Monica and Ross's dad who has a knack for putting his foot in his mouth, often at Judy's expense.
Carol's life partner, often at odds with Ross but ultimately part of the same parenting team.
Ross's short-term girlfriend, a paleontology professor who eventually falls for Joey.
Ross's girlfriend during Rachel's pregnancy, known for her patience until Ross's life became too crazy.
Rachel's handsome, much younger boyfriend when she worked at Ralph Lauren.
Ross's much younger girlfriend, a student of his, known for her playful and youthful nature.
Joey's girlfriend who Chandler falls for, sparking a brief rift between the best friends.
Ross's second wife, an English woman who Ross impulsively proposed to.
Monica's millionaire boyfriend with a surprising interest in becoming the Ultimate Fighting Champion.
